# Environment template guide
#
# Use one of the environment-specific templates:
# - .env.local.example : local development (Docker Postgres)
# - .env.prod.example  : deployment (external Postgres)
#
# Then copy the selected template to `.env`.
#
# PowerShell:
#   Copy-Item .env.local.example .env
#   Copy-Item .env.prod.example .env
#
# Bash:
#   cp .env.local.example .env
#   cp .env.prod.example .env
#
# Shared key contract reference:
# - DATABASE_URL (required)
# - DATABASE_DRIVER (optional, psycopg2|psycopg)
# - DB_SSLMODE (optional, disable|allow|prefer|require|verify-ca|verify-full)
# - ENV (dev|prod|test)
# - APP_ENV (local|prod)
# - CORS_ALLOW_ORIGINS (optional)
# - OPENAI_API_KEY, LLM_MODEL, LLM_TEMPERATURE, LLM_MAX_TOKENS (optional)
# - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET, GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI (optional)
# - JWT_SECRET_KEY, JWT_REFRESH_SECRET, COOKIE_SECURE (optional)
